item.title: Creality Halot One Printer - Resin Vat Cover
item.description:
This is a resin vat cover for the Creality Halot One (CL60) MSLA resin printer.

It allows you to cover the resin to protect it from accidental exposure to dust or UV rays.

The design clears the captive screws of the Halot One's vat and can be used while the vat is still attached to the printer.

The design includes a 1/4"-20 thread for the optional handle.

Fusion (F3D) and STEP files are included if you wish to remix this. Please reference this original design when posting makes or remixes.

item.title: Reggi asta bagno parametrico
item.description:
Soluzione regolabile e carina per ogni esigenza di altezza e per diametro l'asta della tenda del bagno.

Il progetto è stato creato per diverse altezze
-regolabile da 209mm a 335mm senza prolunghe
-regolabile da 335mm a 460mm con 1 prolunga standard
-regolabile da 460mm a 585mm con 2 prolunga standard
-regolabile da 585mm a 709mm con 3 prolunga standard

Creato il progetto parametrico con la possibilità di cambiare il diametro del tubo e l'altezza della lunghezza del tubo:
1- stampare il semplice calibro e capire il tubo (oppure utilizzare un calibro)
1.1-ci sono anche le misure standard dell' OCCHIELLO 21mm 26mm 31mm
2- aprire il file immagine e seguire le istruzioni
2.1-modificare tutto OCCHIELLO (altezza, larghezza, profondità e diametro)
2.2-modificare la PROLUNGA (H altezza)

item.title: Chamber Flag for Mossberberg 12 gauge Maverick 88 / 500
item.description:
Chamber safety flag for 12 gauge Mossberg Maverick 88. Should also work on 500 and 590 as I believe they have near identical receivers.

Will probably work on some other 12 gauge shotguns from other manufacturers if they have the extractor in the same place so long as the receiver isn't surrounded by an inch of plastic molding.

Model has threads for a bore swab insert but it's not required. M7x1 thread fits the mops that come with Carlson's snap caps and I have read that Hoppe's should fit but have not tested. Other brands may use different thread pitch. Would be happy to model versions with other thread pitches if you know what size and pitch you need.

I believe this is my final revision. Made a few changes and I'm currently printing this version but I don't expect any issues.

item.title: SKR Pro v1.2 Active Cooling Duct and 5015 Fan Mount
item.description:
An elegant fan duct design for cooling your stepper drivers on the BTT SKR Pro v1.2. The duct just snaps right onto the fan and then the fan is bolted onto the mount which is attached via standoffs to the board.

Parts:

Provided heatsinks mounted on the drivers (mine are blue with the TMC 2209 drivers)
1x 5015 Blower Fan
2x 10mm Standoffs with bolt and nut. Mine are nylon and can be seen in one of the photos. (for fan mount)
2x M3 25mm Bolt and nut (for fan)

Plugs into the Controller Fan Header (Fan 2 header in my case)

Easily remixable for similar BTT boards so I have included step and f3d files to fit your needs.

item.title: Cup Organizer
item.description:
This is an organizer that is designed to organize two cups in a vertical position.
Cups like coffee mugs are not easy to organize since they have handles. Or some other cups with special shape also leads to the same problem.

The first thing that came to my mind is a round disk in which both sides could hold the cup's open edge. However, it may not able to fit in cups with different diameters. Then I tried to find some solution with more versatility.

I need to find some mechanism that could change its dimension in one direction by a motion in the other direction. Then the four-bar linkage mechanism came to my mind. Thus this organizer comes out with the combination of three sets of four-bar linkage mechanisms.

The plates of the organizer come in two different shapes. Besides, the dimensions of the shaft and holes may vary from different printing setups, some adjustments may need to be done to make the shaft and hole fit. In order to keep the axial position of the parts, it's better to keep the texture of the 3D printed shaft and holes.
item.author: winfordew

item.title: Gloomhaven JOTL token basket
item.description:
Basket to hold the damage tokens for Gloomhaven Jaws of the Lion. As the pictures show, the monster card and monster devider thing slide inside the basket. The little edges make sure that the tokens don't get mixed up. Besides that, there is a little bit of extra space around the monster card to fit a larger amount of tokens and muddle/strengthen/poison things.

I designed a basket for 6 and 10 monsters. Make sure to print it flat and use supports. Also make sure to remove all the supports with a scraper or something otherwise the monster card will not fit perfectly.

In the picture not all supports we removed yet, therefore it is not all fitting correctly.

I printed this in black PETG but PLA would also work fine.
